WEBVTT

01:32.500 --> 01:34.502
[Children giggle]

03:35.124 --> 03:36.626
[Police radio drones]

03:39.128 --> 03:40.129
License, please.

03:40.129 --> 03:42.131
Is there some sort
of problem, officer?

03:42.131 --> 03:43.633
Your right
headlight's out.

03:43.633 --> 03:45.634
Yeah, I know. I've been
meaning to get it fixed,

03:45.634 --> 03:47.636
But with
the holidays and all...

03:47.636 --> 03:49.638
All right.

03:49.638 --> 03:50.639
Cold night.

03:55.644 --> 03:57.145
Ok. Stay sober.

04:16.666 --> 04:17.666
[Tires squeal]

04:17.666 --> 04:19.168
[Horn honks]

05:07.717 --> 05:08.718
[Rock music plays]

05:12.722 --> 05:14.724
[Auld Lang Syne plays]

05:38.247 --> 05:39.248
[Party horn blares]

05:41.250 --> 05:43.753
Happy new year!

06:04.775 --> 06:06.276
[Whistling]

06:17.287 --> 06:18.789
I've got it.

06:18.789 --> 06:22.792
Listen, if he's not here
in 5 minutes, I'm gone.

06:40.811 --> 06:41.812
[Car horn honks]

06:41.812 --> 06:42.813
[Party horns toot]

07:01.332 --> 07:02.333
Aah!

07:02.333 --> 07:04.335
Aah!

07:37.368 --> 07:41.372
[Horn honks]

08:11.402 --> 08:12.403
TV: who gives you
the most money?

08:12.403 --> 08:13.404
Donny, that's who.

08:13.905 --> 08:15.406
Do you know it's 7 below
in my window?

08:15.406 --> 08:17.909
Oh, man, the white stuff
is a-Comin' down.

08:17.909 --> 08:18.910
We just got word
from the boys

08:19.410 --> 08:20.912
At the weather bureau
that with the wind chill,

08:20.912 --> 08:23.414
We're talkin'
a cool 40 below.

08:23.915 --> 08:25.416
Good god!
So stay below--

08:31.923 --> 08:32.924
Rob.

08:32.924 --> 08:34.424
Mmm?

08:34.424 --> 08:35.927
It's 40 below.

08:37.929 --> 08:39.429
Stay in bed.

08:42.933 --> 08:44.435
I have an audition.

08:48.440 --> 08:50.442
I'll give you
an audition.

08:58.950 --> 08:59.951
Rob....

09:01.452 --> 09:02.453
Wait. My kid brother.

09:02.954 --> 09:04.455
Oh, he's asleep.

09:04.455 --> 09:05.456
He's right there.

09:05.456 --> 09:07.458
Who cares?

09:07.458 --> 09:09.460
Go back to sleep.

09:11.462 --> 09:12.964
Ohh.

09:16.467 --> 09:17.969
He's going home
in a few days.

09:33.485 --> 09:35.487
Where's my
new headshot?

09:35.487 --> 09:36.989
Did you
print it up yet?

09:36.989 --> 09:38.991
Oh, shit.

09:38.991 --> 09:40.492
Rob.

09:40.492 --> 09:44.496
I'll do it right after
I finish my coffee.

09:44.496 --> 09:46.999
I have an audition
in 45 minutes.

09:46.999 --> 09:48.500
What is this?

09:48.500 --> 09:51.502
You never should have told me
you were gonna do it

09:51.502 --> 09:53.004
If you weren't gonna do it.

09:53.004 --> 09:55.007
I'm sorry. I forgot.

09:55.007 --> 09:56.008
How could you forget?

09:56.008 --> 09:58.010
You've been sitting around
watching football all weekend

09:58.010 --> 09:59.011
With my brother.

09:59.011 --> 10:00.012
I just forgot.

10:00.012 --> 10:01.513
It happens,
for christ's sake.

10:01.513 --> 10:03.015
It's nothing
to get ticked about.

10:03.015 --> 10:05.017
Who's ticked?

10:05.017 --> 10:06.018
Oh!

10:08.020 --> 10:09.021
Don't worry about it.

10:09.521 --> 10:11.023
I'll call the landlord.

10:11.023 --> 10:12.024
Right.

10:12.024 --> 10:14.026
You can't call him.

10:14.526 --> 10:15.527
We're behind
in the rent.

10:15.527 --> 10:18.030
Hey, I wasn't sleeping
too loud for you guys,

10:18.030 --> 10:19.031
Was I?

10:19.031 --> 10:21.533
No, Roland. Here.
Have some coffee.

10:23.035 --> 10:24.536
Stop it.

10:24.536 --> 10:27.539
I don't even
look like this anymore.

10:56.068 --> 10:58.070
My roommate went in
a while ago.

10:58.070 --> 11:00.072
Oh, yeah?
What'd she say?

11:00.072 --> 11:02.074
The pay's good.
He was nice to her.

11:02.074 --> 11:03.075
Man: 59.

11:03.075 --> 11:04.077
59, please.

11:04.077 --> 11:06.079
Oh, that's me.
See you.

11:06.079 --> 11:07.080
Bye.

11:25.598 --> 11:27.100
Hi.

11:27.100 --> 11:29.102
I'm Katie McGovern.

11:29.102 --> 11:31.104
Hi. I'm number 59.

11:31.104 --> 11:33.606
I'll be with you
in a mo--

11:38.111 --> 11:39.612
Oh, well, you're, uh...

11:42.615 --> 11:44.617
Is something wrong?

11:44.617 --> 11:46.119
Oh, no.

11:46.119 --> 11:48.121
No, it's
just that, uh...

11:48.121 --> 11:49.622
Uh, say something.

11:50.123 --> 11:51.624
Tell me something
about yourself.

11:54.127 --> 11:55.628
I did--Uh, I have--

11:55.628 --> 11:57.130
I did an under 5
on all my children.

11:57.630 --> 11:59.632
I have 2
commercials running.

11:59.632 --> 12:02.135
I toured in
taming of the shrew--

12:02.135 --> 12:04.637
Yes, yes, yes,
yes, um....

12:04.637 --> 12:07.640
Would you mind
turning to your left

12:07.640 --> 12:09.142
Just for a moment?

12:10.143 --> 12:11.144
Sure.

12:12.646 --> 12:15.149
Oh, your hair.

12:15.649 --> 12:17.151
Tell me,
does it, um...

12:17.651 --> 12:19.653
Go up?

12:27.161 --> 12:28.661
How's that?

12:31.164 --> 12:32.665
Well...

12:33.666 --> 12:35.168
That's that.

12:38.171 --> 12:40.673
Maybe you read about it
in the trades, hmm?

12:41.174 --> 12:41.674
No.

12:42.175 --> 12:43.676
No? Well...

12:43.676 --> 12:45.178
She and the director

12:45.178 --> 12:46.679
Were at each other's
throats.

12:46.679 --> 12:48.182
Finally,
she left the set.

12:48.182 --> 12:49.683
Oh.

12:49.683 --> 12:51.685
Everybody thought
she would settle down

12:51.685 --> 12:53.187
And come back
and finish the film,

12:53.187 --> 12:55.189
But it has been
a week now,

12:55.189 --> 12:56.690
And they are stuck.

12:57.191 --> 12:58.192
Have they closed down
the production?

12:58.192 --> 12:59.693
Oh, no.

12:59.693 --> 13:00.694
They're up
in Canada,

13:00.694 --> 13:02.196
Shooting every foot
of every scene

13:02.196 --> 13:03.697
In which
she's not involved,

13:03.697 --> 13:05.699
But, you see,
she is the lead.

13:05.699 --> 13:07.701
There is only so much
they can do without her,

13:07.701 --> 13:09.203
So they must
find somebody

13:09.703 --> 13:11.205
As quickly as possible

13:11.205 --> 13:13.207
To fill her role.
To finish--

13:13.207 --> 13:15.209
Are you offering me
the part?

13:15.209 --> 13:17.711
I am offering you
a chance at it.

13:17.711 --> 13:20.714
You will have to go
upstate for a few days,

13:20.714 --> 13:22.216
Where we will
make you over.

13:22.216 --> 13:24.218
You'll do a scene
on videotape.

13:24.218 --> 13:25.719
That's so
the director can see

13:25.719 --> 13:27.721
What you look like
on the screen.

13:28.222 --> 13:31.225
Now, for that,
you would be paid...

13:31.225 --> 13:32.726
Here. $3,000.

13:32.726 --> 13:34.228
It's spelled out here--

13:34.228 --> 13:36.230
The payment schedules,
the release forms,

13:36.230 --> 13:37.731
The union papers.

13:37.731 --> 13:39.233
Everything's covered.

13:39.733 --> 13:40.734
I will send a copy
of that

13:40.734 --> 13:41.735
To your agent
this afternoon.

13:43.237 --> 13:46.240
I'm sort of in between
agents right now.

13:46.240 --> 13:47.741
I see.

13:47.741 --> 13:51.745
What happens if the director
doesn't like me?

13:51.745 --> 13:53.747
But he's going
to like you.

13:53.747 --> 13:55.749
I'm sure of it.

13:55.749 --> 13:56.751
And when you
get the role,

13:56.751 --> 13:59.254
You'll be paid
$9,000 more.

14:00.255 --> 14:02.757
Do you have
some obligation

14:02.757 --> 14:04.759
That prevents you
from taking this?

14:06.261 --> 14:08.763
No. No, not at all.

14:08.763 --> 14:09.764
[Camera clicks]

14:10.265 --> 14:11.766
Rob, this is a role.

14:11.766 --> 14:13.268
It's real.
I'm an actress.

14:13.268 --> 14:15.769
Actresses act.
Waitresses wait tables.

14:15.769 --> 14:16.770
[Click click]

14:16.770 --> 14:19.773
When did you ever
turn down a job?

14:19.773 --> 14:21.275
What's this guy
Murray like?

14:21.775 --> 14:23.777
I don't know.
I just met him.

14:23.777 --> 14:25.279
What's he look like?

14:25.279 --> 14:26.280
How old is he?

14:26.280 --> 14:28.282
Rob, I just met the guy.

14:28.282 --> 14:30.284
I didn't card him.

14:30.284 --> 14:31.286
What's got into you?

14:31.786 --> 14:33.288
Just asking.

14:33.788 --> 14:34.789
Will you put
that thing down?!

14:36.791 --> 14:40.795
Look, Katie, if you want
to do this thing, just do it.

14:42.297 --> 14:43.298
[Horn honks]

14:50.805 --> 14:52.807
That's him.

14:56.311 --> 14:57.312
I'm going.

15:02.317 --> 15:04.319
I gave you
the number, right?

15:04.319 --> 15:05.821
Mm-Hmm.

15:10.325 --> 15:11.826
So...

15:13.328 --> 15:15.830
I'll call you
when I get there.

15:15.830 --> 15:17.332
Great.

15:27.342 --> 15:29.844
We'll talk
about this then.

15:29.844 --> 15:31.846
Great.

15:31.846 --> 15:34.349
[Click click]

15:37.352 --> 15:39.354
Hey, sis,
leaving us already?

15:39.354 --> 15:40.356
Yep.

15:40.856 --> 15:41.857
My classes start
Wednesday,

15:41.857 --> 15:43.359
So I may not be here
when you get--

15:43.859 --> 15:44.860
Back.

15:47.363 --> 15:48.364
Something I said?

15:58.374 --> 16:00.875
[Click click click]

16:04.879 --> 16:07.382
[Click click click]

16:10.885 --> 16:13.888
[Click click click]

16:15.391 --> 16:16.392
Aah!

16:42.918 --> 16:43.919
Oh, dear.

16:43.919 --> 16:45.921
What's the matter?

16:46.422 --> 16:48.924
I hope Dr. Lewis
won't be worried.

16:48.924 --> 16:51.427
Who's Dr. Lewis?

16:51.427 --> 16:52.928
The producer.

16:52.928 --> 16:55.931
He's arranged for you
to stay at his house.

16:55.931 --> 16:57.933
He's a doctor?

16:57.933 --> 17:00.436
He doesn't
practice anymore.

17:00.436 --> 17:01.437
Since
his retirement,

17:01.437 --> 17:02.938
He's turned
his attention

17:02.938 --> 17:05.941
To other pursuits.

17:15.951 --> 17:18.454
How much further?

17:18.954 --> 17:20.955
Just the next town.

17:25.962 --> 17:27.464
It's beautiful.

17:31.468 --> 17:33.470
The storm,
the pine trees...

17:33.970 --> 17:36.973
[Sighs]
it's like a dream.

17:38.475 --> 17:39.476
[Knock on window]

17:40.977 --> 17:41.978
$12.50.

17:42.479 --> 17:43.480
Oh.
[Chuckles]

17:44.980 --> 17:46.982
Hold on a second.

18:06.503 --> 18:09.005
Free goldfish with
every $10 purchase.

18:09.506 --> 18:11.508
Goldfish?

18:11.508 --> 18:13.510
Well, well, well.

18:13.510 --> 18:15.512
Uh, would you
hold on to that?

18:17.013 --> 18:19.516
Poor things.

18:53.550 --> 18:55.552
[Piano plays]

18:56.553 --> 18:58.054
We're here!

18:59.556 --> 19:01.057
We're here!

19:25.082 --> 19:28.586
You made it
through the storm.

19:28.586 --> 19:30.587
Oh, forgive me, my dear.

19:30.587 --> 19:34.090
These contraptions take
some getting used to.

19:36.092 --> 19:38.094
The piano
is automated...

19:40.096 --> 19:41.598
And so am I.

19:43.100 --> 19:45.603
Miss McGovern,
I presume.

19:45.603 --> 19:47.104
It's nice to meet you.

19:47.104 --> 19:49.106
I'm Dr. Joseph Lewis.

19:49.607 --> 19:51.108
The pleasure
is all mine.

19:54.111 --> 19:55.613
Well done, Mr. Murray.

19:56.113 --> 19:57.615
Wonderful.

19:58.115 --> 19:59.116
Thank you.

20:00.618 --> 20:02.620
Take the woman's coat,
why don't you?

20:05.122 --> 20:07.124
And whatever that is...

20:07.625 --> 20:08.125
The goldfish.

20:08.626 --> 20:10.628
A gift from
the gas station.

20:10.628 --> 20:12.129
Do you have
a bowl for them?

20:12.129 --> 20:14.632
Oh, I'm sure we can
find something suitable.

20:16.133 --> 20:18.637
Quite a house.

20:18.637 --> 20:19.137
Quite a house.

20:20.138 --> 20:22.139
Be it ever so humble.

20:22.640 --> 20:25.643
Doesn't look
so humble to me.

20:25.643 --> 20:26.644
I'll give you
the grand tour,

20:26.644 --> 20:27.645
If you like.

20:27.645 --> 20:29.647
Oh, yes, please.

20:31.148 --> 20:34.151
Well, that's
a sorella oil there,

20:34.151 --> 20:36.153
One of the old masters.

20:37.655 --> 20:38.656
Oh, by the way,

20:38.656 --> 20:42.159
The piano was made
for president Mckinley.

20:42.660 --> 20:44.662
He never heard it
play, though.

20:45.162 --> 20:46.664
Shot dead in buffalo

20:46.664 --> 20:49.166
The day it was delivered
to the white house.

20:50.167 --> 20:52.671
Oh, I see.

20:52.671 --> 20:54.673
Shot dead, huh?

20:58.677 --> 21:00.679
We are fortunate
to be back here

21:00.679 --> 21:02.180
In the forest--

21:02.180 --> 21:04.182
Plenty of firewood,

21:04.182 --> 21:07.185
So we keep
the fire going

21:07.185 --> 21:09.187
All through winter.

21:11.189 --> 21:13.691
Oh, that's one
of my passions.

21:13.691 --> 21:15.192
Do you play?

21:15.192 --> 21:17.695
I used to play
my kid brother.

21:17.695 --> 21:18.696
And?

21:18.696 --> 21:20.197
I gave it up.

21:20.197 --> 21:21.198
Why?

21:21.198 --> 21:23.701
He started
to beat me.

21:24.201 --> 21:25.703
How very rude of him.

21:28.707 --> 21:29.708
Oh!

21:30.208 --> 21:31.710
[Chuckles]

21:31.710 --> 21:33.211
Nothing to be
alarmed about.

21:33.211 --> 21:35.213
He's quite dead,
believe me.

21:35.213 --> 21:37.716
I killed him myself.

21:39.217 --> 21:40.719
There's really
nothing like it.

21:41.219 --> 21:43.722
Just you, the bear,
and the cold--

21:44.222 --> 21:45.724
Quite a challenge.

21:45.724 --> 21:48.226
Yeah. I imagine.

21:49.728 --> 21:52.731
"To my favorite
impresario."

21:55.233 --> 21:57.235
Please watch your step!

21:58.737 --> 22:01.741
We have mice,
I'm afraid.

22:01.741 --> 22:04.243
They come into the house
every winter...

22:04.744 --> 22:06.745
For the warmth,
I suppose.

22:07.245 --> 22:09.247
We have traps
all over.

22:09.748 --> 22:10.749
Mice, bears...

22:10.749 --> 22:12.751
Is there anything else
I should know about?

22:12.751 --> 22:15.253
Ha ha ha ha.

22:16.254 --> 22:18.256
My bedroom
is back there,

22:18.256 --> 22:20.258
And the downstairs
bathroom.

22:21.760 --> 22:25.263
Your guest room
is upstairs.

22:28.266 --> 22:30.769
Ah, just lovely.

22:37.276 --> 22:38.778
Our dining room.

22:43.783 --> 22:45.284
Mr. Murray has served

22:45.284 --> 22:47.787
Many an extraordinary
meal in here.

22:47.787 --> 22:49.288
If he doesn't stop it,

22:49.288 --> 22:50.790
They will have to
carry me around

22:50.790 --> 22:52.291
In a forklift.

22:52.291 --> 22:54.794
Ha ha ha ha ha ha.

22:58.797 --> 23:00.799
Could I use the phone?

23:00.799 --> 23:03.301
But of course.

23:08.306 --> 23:09.307
Dr. Lewis?

23:09.307 --> 23:10.810
Yes?

23:10.810 --> 23:12.311
There's
no dial tone.

23:12.812 --> 23:14.814
Are you sure?

23:14.814 --> 23:15.815
Yes.

23:15.815 --> 23:17.316
Oh, the storm.

23:17.316 --> 23:19.318
Of course.

23:19.318 --> 23:21.320
The lines must be down.

23:21.320 --> 23:23.823
If the lines
aren't up by morning,

23:24.323 --> 23:26.325
Mr. Murray will
drive you into town.

23:32.832 --> 23:35.835
Her name is Julie rose.

23:39.338 --> 23:41.340
She could be my sister.

23:41.340 --> 23:43.342
That's why
you are here.

23:46.346 --> 23:48.849
She just
walked off the set?

23:53.853 --> 23:55.855
Worse yet, I'm afraid.

23:55.855 --> 23:57.857
I heard from the director
this morning.

23:59.358 --> 24:00.860
She had
a nervous breakdown.

24:00.860 --> 24:04.864
He says she'll never
be the same again.

24:04.864 --> 24:06.866
Oh.

24:06.866 --> 24:08.868
That's awful.

24:08.868 --> 24:10.369
Of course it is.

24:10.369 --> 24:11.871
But it's you

24:11.871 --> 24:14.874
We are counting on now,
miss McGovern,

24:14.874 --> 24:18.879
And we must do everything
to get you ready.

24:18.879 --> 24:20.881
What is this?

24:21.381 --> 24:23.884
It's your scene
for the videotape.

24:23.884 --> 24:26.386
Start learning it
tonight.

24:26.386 --> 24:28.889
It's a thriller?

24:30.390 --> 24:31.892
Yes, exactly.

24:32.893 --> 24:34.895
We'll shoot it tomorrow,

24:35.395 --> 24:37.397
And we have it ready
for the director

24:37.898 --> 24:39.900
The moment he arrives.

24:39.900 --> 24:42.903
You are going to
have to be perfect,

24:42.903 --> 24:43.903
Miss McGovern.

24:45.905 --> 24:46.906
Your face...

24:48.407 --> 24:49.408
Your hair...

24:50.910 --> 24:52.912
Your smile.

24:52.912 --> 24:56.416
Everything
has to be just right.

24:59.920 --> 25:01.421
I'm all yours.

25:51.471 --> 25:52.973
Miss McGovern?

25:53.473 --> 25:54.975
It's Mr. Murray,
miss McGovern.

25:54.975 --> 25:56.476
Just a second.

26:00.480 --> 26:01.982
I brought you
some warm milk.

26:02.483 --> 26:05.486
I know how hard it is
to sleep in a strange place

26:05.987 --> 26:06.988
The first night.

26:06.988 --> 26:07.989
Uh-Huh.

26:09.490 --> 26:11.492
Oh, well.

26:11.492 --> 26:12.493
Thanks.

26:14.495 --> 26:15.997
Miss McGovern?

26:15.997 --> 26:17.498
Yeah?

26:17.498 --> 26:19.500
I just wanted to say...

26:21.502 --> 26:24.005
I think Dr. Lewis
likes you.

26:26.507 --> 26:28.009
Well, thanks.

26:28.009 --> 26:31.011
Well, he doesn't
like everyone, you know.

26:31.011 --> 26:33.013
He doesn't?

26:33.013 --> 26:34.514
Oh, gracious me, no.

26:36.016 --> 26:37.518
But he likes you.

26:37.518 --> 26:40.021
I can tell.

26:40.021 --> 26:42.023
Well...

26:42.023 --> 26:44.025
I'm sure he likes you,
too, Mr. Murray.

26:46.027 --> 26:47.528
Do you really think so?

26:47.528 --> 26:51.032
Oh, yeah.
Of course he does.

26:53.034 --> 26:55.536
That's very nice
of you to say.

27:00.541 --> 27:02.543
Oh, sweet dreams.

27:02.543 --> 27:03.544
Good night.

27:03.544 --> 27:04.545
Good night.

27:10.051 --> 27:13.555
Mr. Murray,
this knife is dull.

27:13.555 --> 27:16.058
A dull knife
will never do.

27:16.058 --> 27:17.559
I have
a sharpening stone.

27:17.559 --> 27:19.061
Then you better use it.

27:24.565 --> 27:28.069
If you wish to master
your trade, Mr. Murray,

27:28.069 --> 27:31.572
You must first master
the tools of your trade.

27:42.583 --> 27:44.085
Sharp knife, no tears.

27:44.085 --> 27:45.586
Works every time.

27:51.093 --> 27:53.595
[Car engine
won't start]

28:04.106 --> 28:06.608
Can we phone a gas station
and get a jump?

28:06.608 --> 28:07.609
Phone lines...

28:07.609 --> 28:10.112
Oh. Still down. Right.

28:26.628 --> 28:28.630
[Whistling]

28:39.641 --> 28:41.643
How did you
meet Dr. Lewis?

28:44.146 --> 28:46.648
It was a professional
relationship.

28:46.648 --> 28:50.652
What kind of
professional relationship?

28:52.654 --> 28:54.156
I was his patient.

28:58.661 --> 29:00.163
What kind
of doctor is he?

29:01.664 --> 29:03.666
Psychiatrist.

29:14.676 --> 29:16.178
Now, there.

29:17.679 --> 29:20.682
Remarkable, Mr. Murray.

29:20.682 --> 29:23.685
She is Julie rose.

29:34.697 --> 29:36.699
Do you think I should
keep this coat on

29:36.699 --> 29:38.201
Or take it off?

29:42.705 --> 29:44.207
Sitting or standing?

29:47.710 --> 29:49.212
To your right.

29:49.712 --> 29:51.214
To my right? Ok.

29:54.717 --> 29:55.218
No.

29:59.221 --> 30:01.223
Yes. Perfect.

30:01.223 --> 30:04.727
Do I look directly
into the camera or...

30:04.727 --> 30:06.729
No, off to the right.

30:06.729 --> 30:09.732
Pretend as if
the camera isn't there.

30:13.236 --> 30:15.738
I want to take a beat
after the line,

30:15.738 --> 30:17.240
"There was blood
everywhere."

30:17.240 --> 30:18.741
Is that all right?

30:18.741 --> 30:20.243
Oh, yes. Of course.

30:20.743 --> 30:22.245
Ok, let's do it.

30:25.248 --> 30:30.253
Katie McGovern.
Julie rose. Take one.

30:38.761 --> 30:41.265
I'm sorry.
Did you say action?

30:42.766 --> 30:45.269
Oh. Action, yes.

30:50.274 --> 30:52.775
I was all alone
out there.

30:52.775 --> 30:55.778
Where the hell
were you? I mean--

30:58.281 --> 31:00.783
Sorry...sorry.

31:00.783 --> 31:02.785
It's all right.
It's all right.

31:02.785 --> 31:04.787
Are you going to be
right there?

31:04.787 --> 31:06.789
For--Oh...

31:06.789 --> 31:08.791
Oh, sorry.

31:10.293 --> 31:15.299
Katie McGovern.
Julie rose. Take 2.

31:19.803 --> 31:21.305
Action.

31:25.309 --> 31:27.311
I was all alone
out there.

31:27.311 --> 31:29.813
Where the hell were you?

31:29.813 --> 31:31.815
I mean, all alone.

31:34.818 --> 31:37.321
There wasn't another
soul in sight.

31:38.822 --> 31:41.325
Katie: look what
they did to me.

31:41.325 --> 31:43.826
Will you look
what they did to me?!

31:43.826 --> 31:45.828
[Tape ends--Static]

34:06.972 --> 34:08.474
I was all alone
out there.

34:10.976 --> 34:12.978
Where the hell were you?

34:15.481 --> 34:18.484
I mean, all alone.

34:18.484 --> 34:21.485
There wasn't
another soul in sight.

34:24.489 --> 34:27.992
I waited in the parking lot
until 1:30.

34:30.995 --> 34:33.498
She must have
had me followed.

34:33.498 --> 34:36.501
Oh, god...

34:36.501 --> 34:38.002
I should have known.

34:42.507 --> 34:46.011
I don't know how
he got into the car.

34:46.011 --> 34:48.013
I never even saw him.

34:50.014 --> 34:52.016
First thing I know,

34:52.016 --> 34:55.521
His hands
are around my throat.

34:55.521 --> 34:58.023
I tried...to breathe.

34:58.023 --> 35:00.526
I couldn't breathe.

35:00.526 --> 35:02.528
Then, um...

35:02.528 --> 35:04.530
I must
have blacked out.

35:07.032 --> 35:09.535
He must have thought
I was already dead.

35:11.537 --> 35:14.038
I came to
a couple of hours later.

35:14.539 --> 35:16.041
There was blood everywhere.

35:19.545 --> 35:21.547
Look what
they did to me.

35:22.047 --> 35:25.050
Will you look
what they did to me?!

35:32.558 --> 35:34.059
Hello, Evelyn.

35:34.560 --> 35:37.563
This is the proof,
as promised.

35:38.063 --> 35:40.065
She is alive.

35:40.566 --> 35:42.067
Our game continues.

35:42.568 --> 35:45.571
I will contact you...soon.

35:46.071 --> 35:47.072
Good night.

35:58.585 --> 36:01.087
Dr. Lewis?

36:01.087 --> 36:03.590
[Motor runs
in distance]

36:06.091 --> 36:07.593
Dr. Lewis?

36:13.098 --> 36:15.100
Hello? Is anybody here?

36:18.604 --> 36:20.105
Dr. Lewis?

36:21.106 --> 36:22.107
Dr. Lewis?

37:22.168 --> 37:23.169
[Gasps]

37:29.175 --> 37:32.178
You lied to me.
Why did you lie to me?

37:38.185 --> 37:39.186
Oh, miss McGovern...

37:39.186 --> 37:41.689
We didn't lie to you.

37:41.689 --> 37:42.690
You said she had
a breakdown.

37:42.690 --> 37:44.191
That's a breakdown?

37:44.191 --> 37:47.194
She did
have a breakdown.

37:48.696 --> 37:51.197
She had a breakdown
and then killed herself.

37:58.705 --> 38:00.707
Killed herself?

38:02.208 --> 38:03.710
Yes.

38:11.218 --> 38:13.721
What else haven't
you told me?

38:13.721 --> 38:19.727
Miss McGovern, we didn't
want to upset you.

38:19.727 --> 38:23.731
What happened to Julie rose
was a tragedy.

38:23.731 --> 38:27.735
This movie
was her first big role.

38:27.735 --> 38:32.239
I'm afraid the pressure
was just too much for her.

38:36.744 --> 38:39.246
Perhaps we should
have told you.

38:39.246 --> 38:42.249
But I promise you,

38:42.249 --> 38:44.752
There is nothing else
you don't know.

39:01.268 --> 39:04.772
Suicide is a terrible thing.

39:19.788 --> 39:21.790
[Siren wailing]

39:26.795 --> 39:28.296
Operator recording:
the number you--

39:35.303 --> 39:37.805
The number
you have reached--

39:42.309 --> 39:44.311
Hello.
May I help you?

39:44.311 --> 39:45.312
Yes, operator.
I'm having trouble

39:45.312 --> 39:46.814
Dialing this number.

39:46.814 --> 39:48.816
I wonder if you could
dial it for me, please?

39:49.316 --> 39:50.818
What is the number
you're trying to reach?

39:50.818 --> 39:52.821
Area code 311,

39:52.821 --> 39:54.823
359-28--

39:55.323 --> 39:58.326
Sorry. There's no 311
area code in existence.

39:58.326 --> 39:59.327
Are you sure?

39:59.327 --> 40:02.330
There is no
311 area code.

40:14.342 --> 40:18.847
Castle,
queen's side.

40:19.347 --> 40:22.350
Castle,
king's side.

40:22.851 --> 40:23.852
How can you play

40:24.352 --> 40:25.854
Without looking
at the board?

40:28.857 --> 40:30.859
Memory, my dear.

40:30.859 --> 40:33.862
I could move
my own pieces, but...

40:35.363 --> 40:37.365
I'm lazy.

40:37.866 --> 40:40.368
I prefer to be moved.

40:40.368 --> 40:41.870
[Piano plays]

40:46.875 --> 40:48.877
How did it go on?

40:51.379 --> 40:52.380
Lovely, isn't it?

40:52.881 --> 40:55.383
It's quite ingenious,
actually,

40:55.884 --> 40:59.387
Triggered by
this little device here.

40:59.888 --> 41:01.389
It monitors
my heartbeat constantly.

41:01.891 --> 41:04.393
When my heart
is beating too fast,

41:04.393 --> 41:07.396
It sends a signal
to the piano...

41:07.396 --> 41:10.900
And we have music.

41:10.900 --> 41:12.401
[Fire crackles]

41:14.403 --> 41:18.407
At my age, one needs
to be aware of such things.

41:18.407 --> 41:19.909
When I hear the melody,

41:20.409 --> 41:23.912
I know it's time
to stop my exercising...

41:23.912 --> 41:25.413
And have a rest.

41:25.413 --> 41:27.415
Do you like the piece?

41:31.419 --> 41:33.421
It's Vivaldi...

41:33.421 --> 41:36.926
The four seasons.

41:36.926 --> 41:38.427
Winter.

41:49.438 --> 41:52.441
Mr. Murray: pawn
to queen's rook 3.

42:06.956 --> 42:09.959
Is the house
warm enough for you?

42:11.962 --> 42:14.463
Yes. Fine.

42:14.463 --> 42:16.465
You're shivering.

42:19.969 --> 42:21.971
I'm fine.

42:33.983 --> 42:35.985
Queen to rook 4.

43:24.034 --> 43:25.035
Dr. Lewis, quietly:
Mr. Murray.

43:44.554 --> 43:46.056
Miss McGovern?

43:47.557 --> 43:50.060
The phone's still dead.

43:50.560 --> 43:53.063
Dr. Lewis was
worried about you.

43:54.564 --> 43:57.568
I'm a little tired,
that's all.

43:57.568 --> 44:00.570
Mm-Hmm.
You look pale.

44:02.072 --> 44:06.076
I think I'll go upstairs
and have a nap before dinner.

44:30.101 --> 44:31.602
Malcolm.

44:33.104 --> 44:35.606
Dr. Lewis.

44:56.126 --> 44:57.627
[Pot clangs]

45:01.131 --> 45:02.632
[Snap--Squeak]

45:06.637 --> 45:10.141
We've caught one,
Mr. Murray.

45:12.143 --> 45:13.644
Dispose of
the poor creature

45:13.644 --> 45:15.646
When you
have a chance.

45:32.663 --> 45:34.165
[Footsteps]

48:27.839 --> 48:29.341
Aah!

48:29.341 --> 48:32.345
Dr. Lewis
is looking for you.

48:46.359 --> 48:48.861
[Cup rattling]

48:49.362 --> 48:51.364
What are you
doing to me?

48:51.864 --> 48:54.367
We are not doing
anything to you, dear.

48:56.369 --> 48:57.370
All my I.D.
Is missing

48:57.370 --> 48:58.371
From my wallet--

48:58.371 --> 49:02.375
My bank cards,
my credit cards.

49:02.875 --> 49:04.377
Perhaps you forgot
them in new york.

49:04.377 --> 49:05.878
There's nothing
to be upset about.

49:05.878 --> 49:07.881
I saw
my driver's license

49:07.881 --> 49:09.883
In the fireplace.

49:09.883 --> 49:12.386
You think we burned
your driver's license?

49:12.386 --> 49:14.387
Why on earth
would we ever do--

49:14.387 --> 49:15.888
I don't think anything.

49:15.888 --> 49:16.889
I saw it!

49:24.397 --> 49:27.400
And I saw the phone
in the kitchen.

49:27.400 --> 49:28.901
The lines
aren't down.

49:28.901 --> 49:31.404
The cord's been cut.

49:31.404 --> 49:32.405
Dear, dear, dear.

49:33.906 --> 49:35.908
We pushed you too hard.

49:39.912 --> 49:41.915
Miss McGovern...

49:43.417 --> 49:45.419
Something more
to drink?

49:51.425 --> 49:53.427
Some more
hot chocolate?

50:01.435 --> 50:02.936
Hmm?

50:08.941 --> 50:10.943
You can take the chocolate
back into the kitchen,

50:10.943 --> 50:12.445
Mr. Murray.

50:17.451 --> 50:19.953
The woman does not
appreciate your concern

50:19.953 --> 50:21.455
For her welfare.

50:25.459 --> 50:26.960
Wha--

50:26.960 --> 50:28.462
[Cup falls]

50:28.462 --> 50:30.964
What is it that
you want from me?

50:33.467 --> 50:35.469
I have no money.

50:35.469 --> 50:37.471
I have nothing
to offer you.

50:37.471 --> 50:40.474
My dear, we don't want
anything from you.

50:40.474 --> 50:42.976
It appears you have
some misconceptions

50:42.976 --> 50:44.478
About us,

50:44.478 --> 50:46.480
And obviously,
we had some about you.

50:46.480 --> 50:49.483
I'm afraid you have
disqualified yourself

50:49.483 --> 50:52.987
From further consideration
for this job.

50:52.987 --> 50:55.490
We'll take you home
in the morning.

51:01.495 --> 51:02.496
Home?

51:02.496 --> 51:05.499
You do want to go home?

51:05.499 --> 51:07.000
Oh, yes.

51:07.000 --> 51:09.002
Fine. Then we are
in agreement,

51:09.805 --> 51:11.807
Are we not?
Please...

51:21.817 --> 51:24.320
If you are
afraid of us,

51:24.320 --> 51:26.321
I suggest that
you use the bolt

51:26.821 --> 51:28.823
On the inside of
your bedroom door.

51:28.823 --> 51:30.825
We won't disturb you.

51:35.830 --> 51:38.333
Good night,
miss McGovern.

51:38.333 --> 51:39.834
Much too
cold a night

51:40.335 --> 51:43.338
To be outside
without an overcoat.

51:43.338 --> 51:44.839
Don't you think,
Mr. Murray?

51:44.839 --> 51:45.340
Ha ha ha.

52:23.376 --> 52:25.378
[Chair clunking
on floor]

52:30.883 --> 52:33.386
You're going to do
just fine, Mr. Murray.

52:34.887 --> 52:36.889
You'll do
a perfect job.

52:38.890 --> 52:40.892
How can you be sure?

52:48.399 --> 52:50.401
Because you must.

53:16.876 --> 53:17.877
[Glass shatters]

54:09.877 --> 54:11.379
[Door creaks]

56:09.992 --> 56:12.495
Aah!

56:12.495 --> 56:12.995
Aah!

56:17.498 --> 56:18.999
Aah!

56:20.501 --> 56:22.503
Aah!

56:23.003 --> 56:24.505
In a minute,
Mr. Murray.

56:24.505 --> 56:26.507
Just finish
what you're doing.

56:29.510 --> 56:31.512
Aah! Aah!

56:31.512 --> 56:33.514
Aah!

59:12.666 --> 59:14.167
[Dial tone]

59:14.167 --> 59:16.168
Ohh!

59:28.180 --> 59:30.182
[Rings]

59:33.686 --> 59:35.187
[Rings]

59:38.190 --> 59:40.693
[Rings]

59:44.195 --> 59:45.196
[Rings]

59:45.196 --> 59:46.698
Hello?

59:46.698 --> 59:48.199
[Quietly]
rob?

59:48.199 --> 59:49.200
Rob?

59:49.701 --> 59:50.702
Hello?

59:50.702 --> 59:51.702
Rob...

59:51.702 --> 59:53.203
It's...

59:53.203 --> 59:54.705
Oh, god! Help me!

59:55.205 --> 59:56.707
Katie!
Where are you?

59:56.707 --> 59:57.708
Where are you
calling from?

59:57.708 --> 59:59.209
I--I don't know.

59:59.710 --> 01:00:01.712
I'm calling from
an attic in a house.

01:00:01.712 --> 01:00:02.713
And...

01:00:02.713 --> 01:00:05.215
They c-C-Cut...

01:00:05.716 --> 01:00:08.218
Th-Th-They cut
off my finger.

01:00:08.218 --> 01:00:09.720
What?!

01:00:09.720 --> 01:00:11.221
They cut off
my finger!

01:00:14.725 --> 01:00:16.226
Miss McGovern.

01:00:16.226 --> 01:00:17.728
I'm going to find you,

01:00:17.728 --> 01:00:22.232
But you have to
tell me where you are!

01:00:22.733 --> 01:00:24.234
I don't know.
I don't know where I am.

01:00:24.234 --> 01:00:27.237
Pine...Pineview...
Pinecrest...

01:00:27.237 --> 01:00:28.237
Pine something.

01:00:28.738 --> 01:00:30.239
Rob, they're gonna kill me!

01:00:30.239 --> 01:00:31.240
I know they're gonna kill me!

01:00:34.243 --> 01:00:35.244
What road?!

01:00:35.244 --> 01:00:36.745
The thruway.

01:00:36.745 --> 01:00:38.246
We went upstate
on the thruway.

01:00:40.749 --> 01:00:41.750
Katie, please,

01:00:41.750 --> 01:00:44.753
How long were you
on the thruway?

01:00:44.753 --> 01:00:46.755
Um...a few hours maybe.

01:00:46.755 --> 01:00:47.756
It was dark.
I fell asleep.

01:00:48.256 --> 01:00:50.759
Think, Katie, think.
What was the exit?

01:00:50.759 --> 01:00:53.261
I don't know.
I don't know what exit.

01:00:53.762 --> 01:00:55.263
Um...um...

01:00:55.263 --> 01:00:56.765
There was a bridge.

01:00:56.765 --> 01:00:58.266
There was
a covered bridge.

01:01:01.770 --> 01:01:03.771
Uh...the goldfish!

01:01:03.771 --> 01:01:05.773
It was the next town
after the goldfish.

01:01:05.773 --> 01:01:07.274
Goldfish? What do you
mean, goldfish?

01:01:07.775 --> 01:01:08.776
He gave us a goldfish.

01:01:08.776 --> 01:01:11.278
I remember Mr. Murray said
it was the next town.

01:01:14.782 --> 01:01:15.783
Listen to me!

01:01:15.783 --> 01:01:16.784
Hang up the phone,

01:01:16.784 --> 01:01:19.286
Dial the operator,
and call the police.

01:01:19.286 --> 01:01:20.287
Oh, no, don't go!

01:01:20.287 --> 01:01:22.289
Please don't hang up!

01:01:22.790 --> 01:01:23.290
Tell the police that.

01:01:23.791 --> 01:01:24.792
Tell them everything
you told me!

01:01:25.292 --> 01:01:26.293
They're gonna kill me.
They're gonna kill...

01:01:30.296 --> 01:01:31.798
I'm going to
find you, all right?

01:01:31.798 --> 01:01:32.799
You're going
to be all right.

01:01:32.799 --> 01:01:34.300
Oh...rob...

01:01:34.300 --> 01:01:36.302
Now hang up
and dial the police.

01:01:36.302 --> 01:01:37.804
Please hurry!

01:01:37.804 --> 01:01:39.305
Hang up! Now!

01:01:39.305 --> 01:01:41.306
Please don't go!

01:01:41.306 --> 01:01:41.807
Please don't go!

01:01:43.809 --> 01:01:44.810
Roland!

01:01:48.814 --> 01:01:49.815
Pinehill police,
Sergeant Brody.

01:01:50.315 --> 01:01:52.818
I'm in a house that
belongs to Dr. Lewis.

01:01:52.818 --> 01:01:54.820
He's downstairs.
He's gonna kill me.

01:01:54.820 --> 01:01:56.321
You've got to help me.

01:01:56.321 --> 01:01:57.823
Where is
the house located?

01:01:58.323 --> 01:01:59.324
I don't know.
I don't know.

01:01:59.324 --> 01:02:00.826
Are you in danger
right now?

01:02:00.826 --> 01:02:02.828
Yes.
Yes, I'm in danger!

01:02:02.828 --> 01:02:04.830
They don't know
I've called.

01:02:04.830 --> 01:02:05.831
Please, please hurry!

01:02:05.831 --> 01:02:07.833
If you could just
give me your name.

01:02:07.833 --> 01:02:09.835
Hello? Are you
all right, ma'am?

01:02:09.835 --> 01:02:11.837
Hello?
Are you there?

01:02:11.837 --> 01:02:14.339
Hello? Hello?

01:02:14.339 --> 01:02:15.340
[Dial tone]

01:02:21.845 --> 01:02:23.346
Oh!

01:02:33.857 --> 01:02:35.358
[Gasps]

01:02:46.870 --> 01:02:48.088
Unh!

01:02:49.589 --> 01:02:50.090
Ohh!

01:02:52.091 --> 01:02:53.092
Ow!

01:02:54.093 --> 01:02:55.594
Unh!

01:02:57.096 --> 01:02:58.097
Ow!

01:02:58.097 --> 01:02:59.098
Easy, easy, easy,
easy, easy!

01:03:14.612 --> 01:03:16.114
Blackmail,
miss McGovern,

01:03:16.114 --> 01:03:20.118
Is a game of moves
and countermoves,

01:03:20.118 --> 01:03:22.620
Not unlike chess.

01:03:22.620 --> 01:03:26.124
The players in
this particular game

01:03:26.124 --> 01:03:27.125
Were 2 sisters.

01:03:28.625 --> 01:03:30.127
Several years ago,

01:03:30.127 --> 01:03:33.130
One of them
married for money...

01:03:33.130 --> 01:03:35.632
Then murdered
to keep it.

01:03:37.634 --> 01:03:39.636
The other
saw everything,

01:03:39.636 --> 01:03:41.638
But never
said a word.

01:03:43.140 --> 01:03:44.141
She just vanished

01:03:44.641 --> 01:03:46.143
From her
sister's life...

01:03:48.145 --> 01:03:50.147
And eventually
entered mine...

01:03:52.149 --> 01:03:53.650
As a patient.

01:03:55.652 --> 01:03:57.654
Isn't that right,
Mr. Murray?

01:03:57.654 --> 01:03:58.655
Yes.

01:04:03.660 --> 01:04:04.660
This woman bore

01:04:05.161 --> 01:04:07.162
A remarkable
resemblance to you,

01:04:07.662 --> 01:04:08.663
Miss McGovern.

01:04:12.667 --> 01:04:14.169
Julie rose.

01:04:15.170 --> 01:04:16.671
Precisely.

01:04:20.675 --> 01:04:24.179
She shared the knowledge
of the murder with me

01:04:24.179 --> 01:04:27.682
During one
of our sessions.

01:04:27.682 --> 01:04:30.685
I prescribed
an unorthodox,

01:04:30.685 --> 01:04:33.688
But profitable
form of therapy.

01:04:35.190 --> 01:04:37.192
